The hardest part of the Mage epic is the crown.<br>
<br>
I raised 80k by killing reavers in CoM with friends and eventually selling the Jade Reavers that dropped.  I sold them for 15k each.<br>
<br>
I am down to Earth and Water staffs and since MQs on the server I am on for either of those are usually less then 40k I am not too worried.<br>
<br>
I will get my epic by the New Year.  My thoughts are that the our epic is not really much of an epic.  It would be one thing if there were epic battles like with the Cleric or Cahnter epics.  For us however we have to kill a ton of green mobs then some average MOBs that rarely drop what we need and are located in places folks don't want to go.  <br>
<br>
This makes it more about luck and what guild your in then about Epic battles.  Just my thoughts. <br>
<br>
I have been on well over 30 raids in both Kedge and Hate and have yet to obtain those 2 remaining parts.<br>
<br>
I will try until late December and then just raise funds and MQ.<br>
<br>
Hell I know 1 mage on my server thats been level 60 for 6 months longer then me (I dinged in May) and he has more or less given up short earth and phinny staffs.<br>
<br>
The crown though is rare on my server, so few guilds bother that your lucky to get one for 80k.  Getting to 7th isle in PoA is very hard.  I lead a guild of over 70 people level 46+ and I would never try it with them even if we had 2 times the people.  This is why I bought mine.<br>
<br>
<br>
It is easier to end up on a Hate raid eventually that produces the Earth Staff or to buy the MQ from somone for half what the crown costs then to obtain the crown.<br>
<br>
Just my opinion but if you manage to get the Crown your half way there.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Rthen Majere<br>
Arch Mage<br>
